  "title": "Assistant Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>We are looking for a warm, enthusiastic and responsible Assistant Teacher to support our teaching team in nurturing children aged 3–4 years old (N2 level) in a caring and stimulating kindergarten environment. This role is ideal for individuals who are passionate about working with young children and are keen to build a career in the early childhood sector. </p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assist the teaching team in planning and delivering age-appropriate learning activities for children aged 3–4 years to support their development</li><li>Engage with children to encourage positive social, emotional, and cognitive growth in a safe and nurturing environment</li><li>Support classroom management by maintaining a clean, organized, and stimulating learning space</li><li>Observe and document children’s progress and communicate relevant information to the teaching team for continuous improvement</li><li>Collaborate with colleagues to prepare teaching materials and resources that enhance learning experiences</li><li>Follow health and safety guidelines to ensure the well-being of all children in the kindergarten</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Certificate in ECCE qualification/ EY2 certified/L1 certified</li><li>Fresh Graduates can apply</li></ul><p><strong>We offer:</strong></p><ul><li>Attractive working hours - 8am-1pm </li><li>Mon- Fri (occasional work on Sat- events)</li></ul><p></p>",
